route.soft_comment: Kaboooom! Feels great to do something on my honest second GO that neither Chris Sharma nor Adam Ondra onsighted. Even jimmy "I have a manlier beard" Webb didn't do the moves on this rig. I just don't understand why people line up for short dumpy jug hauls like prohibition, while stellar test pieces like this exist in Colorado. The new la sportiva grip rubber really helped me campus through the crux on this one - especially in the heat! Glad to finally meet my life quota by climbing 14d and psyched to have a few more hard climbs on deck.

I had planned to pontificate on this blatent dumbassery until I realized the unlimited potential in 8a points this allows me. My plan now is to get a 4fer for every route I do. route.fair_comment: Finally Sent this thing today after a lot of work over the years. Took a while to find good beta and even with it the crux is quite hard. Originally a 12c in the guidebook it's possible holds have broken since the FA or perhaps it was sandbagged to begin with. Either way a sampling of any 12c in the park compared with this will leave no doubts that this is for sure more difficult. As this route is essentially just a V6 or V7 boulder problem with a few hard moves at the start and some easy but "don't blow it" moves at the end I think 12d or 13a is fair. Since this is a crimpy route and crimps are my style though, and considering that it took 5 attempts today and probably 25 to 30 attempts over the last two years I think it's far more likely to be 13a than 12d and 13a is what I'm giving it here. Regardless of grade this is a very fun route that deserves more traffic than it currently gets.
